  issued-at: datetime(year: 2026, month: 6, day: 15),
)

It is with great enthusiasm that I recommend Alex Johnson for the doctoral programme in Biomedical Engineering at your institute. I have had the privilege of working with Alex for three years in my department, where they served as a senior research associate on our wearable biosensor validation programme.

Alex joined our team in 2023 and quickly distinguished themselves through exceptional analytical rigour and a remarkable ability to translate complex clinical requirements into actionable research protocols. Their contribution to our Phase II accuracy study was central to the project's success: Alex independently designed the statistical analysis plan, coordinated participant recruitment across three clinical sites, and delivered a final report that met all regulatory standards on the first submission.

Beyond technical competence, Alex demonstrates the collaborative mindset and intellectual curiosity that define a strong researcher. They mentored two junior associates, led weekly journal clubs, and proactively identified a systematic bias in our data-collection pipeline that, once corrected, improved measurement concordance by 4.2 percentage points.

I am confident that Alex will bring the same dedication, creativity, and precision to doctoral research. I recommend them without reservation and believe they will be an asset to any research group fortunate enough to have them. Please do not hesitate to contact me should you require further information.
